                      <section>
                        <title>Start-ups funding is slowing</title>
                        <chapter>
                          <title>Start-ups funding in USA</title>
                          <paragraph>For a long time, it felt like Silicon Valley
                            was the only place to build a successful startup. Now, dozens of other cities
                            are getting in on the game. Yes, the Bay Area, New York, and Boston remain
                            the undisputed centers of the startup world. But new growth in early-stage
                            investment activity, while still small, shifted toward outlying cities in the last year.
                            Overall, the first quarter's fundraising was a "rollercoaster mostly pointed down"
                            for early-stage start-ups.</paragraph>
                          </chapter>
